1
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,900
I met a crazy man once,

2
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:10,198
at a bus-stop outside of
a mental institution,

3
00:00:10,860 --> 00:00:15,260
and we both were looking
at a ladybug.

4
00:00:15,336 --> 00:00:18,351
[I Maybe Crazy But I'm Not Stupid]

5
00:00:18,659 --> 00:00:20,101
And we're both, like, looking,
waiting …

6
00:00:20,101 --> 00:00:22,381
looking at this ladybug,

7
00:00:22,888 --> 00:00:24,751
and I said to him … I said,

8
00:00:24,751 --> 00:00:29,062
“What do you call a male ladybug?”

9
00:00:29,062 --> 00:00:31,845
and he said, “Sir.”

10
00:00:33,323 --> 00:00:35,969
And what he was showing me is like,

11
00:00:35,969 --> 00:00:39,263
“I maybe crazy but I'm not stupid.”

12
00:00:41,127 --> 00:00:45,333
And I thought, “Good point.”

13
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:47,989
I mean, sometimes here, we have

14
00:00:47,989 --> 00:00:51,088
a lot of insect friends

15
00:00:51,165 --> 00:00:53,794
—I just saw a few on the way over—

16
00:00:53,794 --> 00:00:57,788
and sometimes …
and they're in my room,

17
00:00:58,265 --> 00:01:00,023
I like to put them in little containers

18
00:01:00,023 --> 00:01:02,905
and let them go out the window,

19
00:01:02,905 --> 00:01:06,308
but sometimes I look at them

20
00:01:06,739 --> 00:01:10,224
and I imagine they're looking at me,

21
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:15,181
and I think—I don't think I'm better,

22
00:01:15,181 --> 00:01:22,093
but sometimes I am a little surprised

23
00:01:22,740 --> 00:01:25,160
to realise there's a soul

24
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:27,740
animating that insect body,

25
00:01:27,740 --> 00:01:31,735
and what takes you to that plane

26
00:01:32,135 --> 00:01:35,260
scares me, at times.

27
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:36,582
I'm not scared of the insect,

28
00:01:36,582 --> 00:01:38,651
but, like, being one.

29
00:01:39,221 --> 00:01:41,300
But Bhakti Vinod … see that's …

30
00:01:41,300 --> 00:01:42,942
he's not afraid of that.

31
00:01:42,942 --> 00:01:50,237
“Kīṭa-janma hao yathā tuyā dāsa
bahirmukha brahma nāhi janme āśā”;

32
00:01:50,376 --> 00:01:52,551
see a real devotee, Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur,

33
00:01:52,551 --> 00:01:58,583
is saying, “If … I would …
I don't want to be Brahmā

34
00:01:58,861 --> 00:02:02,379
if he's not a devotee.

35
00:02:02,379 --> 00:02:05,435
I'd rather be kīṭa, an insect,

36
00:02:05,435 --> 00:02:08,624
in the house of a devotee.”

37
00:02:08,657 --> 00:02:11,499
That … he's taken on a far, far,

38
00:02:11,499 --> 00:02:14,021
greater, deeper level.

39
00:02:14,021 --> 00:02:16,700
And what does Raghunāth Dās say—

40
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:18,700
the prayojan tattva ācārya?

41
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:21,454
That even the insects in the Dhām

42
00:02:21,669 --> 00:02:26,661
are Mukunda-advaita;

43
00:02:26,661 --> 00:02:28,060
they're dear to Kṛṣṇa

44
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:33,092
because they're helping
promote the pastimes.

45
00:02:33,092 --> 00:02:35,129
But Guru Mahārāj would say,

46
00:02:35,129 --> 00:02:36,882
this kind of vision of seeing

47
00:02:36,882 --> 00:02:40,269
Dhām-vāsīs as liberated souls,

48
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:45,010
that's what he calls “mukta-dṛṣṭi”;

49
00:02:45,618 --> 00:02:49,259
it's the vision of a liberated soul.

50
00:02:49,336 --> 00:02:50,752
Back to that …

51
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:54,261
But we want to be under the influence

52
00:02:54,261 --> 00:02:56,739
of the vision of liberated souls.

53
00:02:56,739 --> 00:02:58,259
Those who can see.

54
00:02:58,259 --> 00:03:02,116
They're seeing properly,
that is the point.

55
00:03:08,106 --> 00:03:12,739
But … relative has it's necessity,

56
00:03:12,739 --> 00:03:16,101
so we're …
But we need to …

57
00:03:16,101 --> 00:03:19,820
Unless you properly conceive the Absolute,

58
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:24,457
then how will you know to adjust the relative?

59
00:03:24,581 --> 00:03:26,541
Adjust it according to what?

60
00:03:26,541 --> 00:03:31,420
There has to be, again, that calibration.

61
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:32,700
According to what?

62
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:33,864
To what standard?

63
00:03:33,864 --> 00:03:35,744
No? All right,
here's the absolute standard,

64
00:03:35,744 --> 00:03:38,004
here we are locally,
adjust it like this.

65
00:03:38,046 --> 00:03:40,087
That'll be acceptable.

